.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBv2s\fP(3f) returns a representation of a numeric \fIvalue\fP as a
string when given a numeric \fIvalue\fP of type REAL, DOUBLEPRECISION,
INTEGER or LOGICAL. It creates the strings using internal \fBWRITE\fP()
statements. Trailing zeros are removed from non-zero values, and the
string is left-justified.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B VALUE
input \fIvalue\fP to be converted to a string
.TP
.B FMT
format can be explicitly given, but is limited to
generating a string of eighty or less characters.
.SH RETURNS
.TP
.B OUTSTR
returned string representing input \fIvalue\fP,
.SH EXAMPLE
Sample Program:
.PP
.nf
.fam C
   program demo_v2s
   use M_strings, only: v2s
   write(*,*) 'The value of 3.0/4.0 is ['//v2s(3.0/4.0)//']'
   write(*,*) 'The value of 1234    is ['//v2s(1234)//']'
   write(*,*) 'The value of 0d0     is ['//v2s(0d0)//']'
   write(*,*) 'The value of .false. is ['//v2s(.false.)//']'
